# Loopin Automation – Project Overview

## What Is This?

A **Playwright + TypeScript UI automation framework** for **Loopin** (formerly branded vHire), an internal HR/hiring platform by Veersa Technologies. The app is hosted as an Azure Static Web App at `https://vhiredev.z22.web.core.windows.net`.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Test framework | Playwright `@playwright/test` (latest) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| Browser | Microsoft Edge (Chromium channel `msedge`) |
| Auth | Microsoft MSAL popup + TOTP MFA via `speakeasy` |
| Config | `dotenv` for env vars |
| CI/CD | Jenkins → Docker (Linux container on Windows host) |
| Reporting | Playwright HTML + custom dashboard reporter + JUnit XML |

## Architecture Pattern

```
Page Object Model (POM) + Data-Driven + Fixture Injection
```

- **Page Objects** encapsulate all locators and interactions (`src/page-objects/`)
- **Test Data** is externalized to JSON files (`src/data/`)
- **Fixtures** inject page objects into tests (`src/fixtures/test.fixture.ts`)
- **Tests** are pure orchestration – no locators, no selectors (`tests/*.spec.ts`)

## Key Directories

```
src/
├── config/          → env.config.ts (env parsing), global-setup.ts (auth bootstrapping)
├── data/            → JSON test data files + test-resume.doc
├── fixtures/        → Playwright fixtures (test.fixture.ts, auth.setup.ts)
├── page-objects/    → POM classes grouped by feature
│   ├── 00-shared/   → BasePage (abstract base for all page objects)
│   ├── 01-login/    → LoginPage
│   ├── 02-requisitions/ → RequisitionListPage, RequisitionFormPage
│   ├── 03-employee-dashboard/ → EmployeeDashboardPage
│   └── 04-referrals/ → ReferralsPage
├── reporters/       → custom-dashboard.reporter.ts
└── utils/           → password-crypto.ts, totp.helper.ts

tests/               → Spec files (01-login, 02-employee-dashboard, 03-requisition, 04-referrals)
scripts/             → Node.js helper scripts (encrypt-password, docker-test, seed-edge-profile)
```

## Numbering Convention

Features are numbered `01-`, `02-`, `03-`, `04-` consistently across page-objects, data files, and test specs. New features should continue the numbering (e.g., `05-interviews`).

## Authentication Model

The organization enforces **Azure AD Conditional Access**, so Playwright's default incognito contexts fail. The solution:

1. **One-time seed**: `npm run seed:profile` opens Edge for manual login → saves profile to `.edge-profile/`
2. **globalSetup**: Uses `chromium.launchPersistentContext()` with the Edge profile, performs automated MSAL + TOTP login, saves `storageState` to `.auth/storage-state.json`
3. **Tests**: Reuse the saved `storageState` via `playwright.config.ts` → no login needed in each test

## Environment Variables (from .env)

| Variable | Required | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `LOOPIN_BASE_URL` | ✅ | App URL |
| `LOOPIN_USERNAME` | ✅ | Microsoft login email |
| `LOOPIN_PASSWORD` or `LOOPIN_PASSWORD_ENCRYPTED` + `LOOPIN_PASSWORD_KEY` | ✅ | Password (plain or AES-256-GCM encrypted) |
| `LOOPIN_TOTP_SECRET` | ✅ | Base32 TOTP secret for MFA |
| `LOOPIN_TIMEOUT` | ✅ | Global test timeout (ms) |
| `LOOPIN_RETRIES` | ❌ | Retry count (default: 2 in CI, 1 locally) |
| `LOOPIN_WORKERS` | ❌ | Parallel workers (default: 1) |
| `LOOPIN_NUKE_PROFILE` | ❌ | Delete Edge profile on startup |
| `LOOPIN_FORCE_FRESH_LOGIN` | ❌ | Force re-login ignoring cached state |

## NPM Scripts

| Command | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `npm test` | Run all tests |
| `npm run test:login` | Run login spec only |
| `npm run test:dashboard` | Run dashboard spec only |
| `npm run test:requisition` | Run requisition spec only |
| `npm run test:referrals` | Run referral spec only |
| `npm run test:ci` | Run all tests in CI mode |
| `npm run seed:profile` | Interactive Edge login for profile seeding |
| `npm run encrypt:password` | Encrypt a password for .env |
| `npm run docker:build` | Build Docker image |
| `npm run docker:test` | Run tests in Docker |

